p%20was%20US%20president%20in%202020%2C%20he%20signed%20executive%20orders%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20accused%20TikTok%2C%20without%20proof%2C%20of%20siphoning%20off%20American%20users'%20data%20to%20benefit%20Beijing%20and%20of%20censoring%20posts%20to%20please%20Chinese%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20decision%20came%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20political%20tension%20between%20Washington%20and%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20failed%20bid%20for%20re-election%2C%20the%20Republican%20campaigned%20on%20an%20anti-China%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20legal%20challenges%20and%20Trump's%20loss%20to%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%2C%20the%20executive%20orders%20did%20not%20take%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBillion%20mark%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202021%2C%20TikTok%20announced%20it%20had%201%20billion%20monthly%20users%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20concerns%20grew%20about%20TikTok%20users%20facing%20risks%20of%20addiction%2C%20propaganda%2C%20and%20spying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20BuzzFeed%20reported%20that%20ByteDance%20employees%20based%20in%20China%20had%20accessed%20non-public%20information%20from%20TikTok%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EByteDance%20tried%20to%20cool%20privacy%20concerns%20by%20hosting%20user%20data%20on%20servers%20managed%20in%20the%20United%20States%20by%20Oracle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20did%20not%20ease%20concerns%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20TikTok%20was%20banned%20from%20devices%20used%20by%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20array%20of%20other%20government%20agencies%20and%20academic%20institutes%20followed%20suit%2C%20forbidding%20members%20from%20using%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETikTok's%20Singaporean%20chief%20executive%20Shou%20Zi%20Chew%20was%20grilled%20by%20members%20of%20the%20US%20Congress%20during%20a%206-hour%20hearing%20in%20March%20of%202023.%3C