d%20livestream%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20new%20business%20aims%20to%20innovate%20traditional%20joss%20paper%20products%20to%20appeal%20to%20younger%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-helps-choose-right-size-packaging-materials-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epackaging%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-crisis-marketing-pr-jobs-economy-consumers-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esustainability%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20this%20year%2C%20they%20were%20approached%20by%20MullenLowe%2C%20an%20advertising%20agency%2C%20to%20develop%20an%20eco-friendly%20hell%20note.%20The%20%26quot%3BEco%20Hell%20Note%26quot%3B%20has%20a%20denomination%20with%2048%20zeroes%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largest%20possible%20denomination%20of%20money%20in%20the%20Chinese%20language.%20Instead%20of%20burning%20a%20stack%20of%20notes%2C%20burning%20one%20piece%20would%20suffice.%20Teo%20added%20that%20their%20note%20is%20ashless%20and%20smokeless%2C%20unlike%20traditional%20notes%20that%20create%20smog%20when%20burned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBurning%20joss%20paper%20is%20deep-rooted%20in%20our%20Chinese%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20ban%20on%20the%20practice%20is%20unlikely%20to%20happen%20despite%20frequent%20complaints.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20have%20to%20come%20out%20with%20a%20compromise%20to%20control%20the%20pollution%20and%20not%20become%20obsolete%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeo%2C%20who%20sources%20the%20paper%20from%20China%2C%20said%20the%20team%20had%20to%20experiment%20with%20different%20types%20of%20paper%20to%20determine%20which%20material%20is%20the%20most%20eco-friendly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20such%20products%20doesn't%20come%20cheap.%20Although%20they%20have%20not%20decided%20on%20a%20price%20for%20their%20Eco%20Hell%20Note%2C%20their%20eco-friendly%20products%20are%20sl